President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Louisiana due to severe storms and flooding from May 18 to June 20, 2015. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The affected parishes include Bossier, Caddo, Grant, Natchitoches, and Red River. William J. Doran III has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the area. Additional designations may be made if requested by the state and based on further damage assessments.